§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We want to add repeatedly. ⦉
⦉

§ Definitiong result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ For each natural number $m$, there exists a function $p_m:
    ω → ω$ which satisfies
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ p_m(0) = 0 \quad \text{ and } \quad p_m(\ssuc{n}) =
        \ssuc{(p_m(n))} + m ⦉
    ⦉
    for every natural number $n$. ⦉
</statement>
<proof>
  ‖ The proof uses the recursion theorem (see␣
    <a href='/sheets/recursion_theorem.html'>
      ‖ Recursion Theorem ⦉
    </a>
    ).
    † ⦊
      ‖ Future editions will give the entire account. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</proof>
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $m$ and $n$ be natural numbers. ⦉

  ‖ The value $p_m(n)$ is the ❬product❭ of $m$ with $n$. ⦉
⦉

