<statement type='proposition' text='Associativity'>
  ‖ Let $k$, $m$, and $n$ be natural numbers. Then
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ (k · m) · n = k · (m · n). ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $m$ and $n$ be natural numbers. Then
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ m · n = n · m. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>

